{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"393e1531-bb8c-4317-9ad7-b68b0aa7eab5","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x removed VSTest support entirely.**\n\nIn 3.x the SDK already defaulted to Microsoft.Testing.Platform but still allowed opting back in with `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`. Starting with 4.0, that property is gone — the VSTest adapter is no longer shipped, so `vstest.console.exe` finds zero tests.\n\n### Fix: switch your CI to `dotnet test`\n\n`dotnet test` works with Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively. Ensure your project enables the integration:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <!-- enables 'dotnet test' bridge to Microsoft.Testing.Platform -->\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThen replace `vstest.console MyTests.dll` with:\n\n```\ndotnet test MyProject.csproj\n```\n\nThis is the supported path going forward — `vstest.console` is no longer compatible with MSTest.Sdk 4.x projects.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"66c21ff8-baf7-4764-bf0b-07133f0116e2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a well-known breaking change in MSTest SDK. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4 (or around that version), the MSTest SDK switched from using the VSTest runner to the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) runner by default. In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, VSTest support was completely removed or disabled by default.\n\nThe key change: **MSTest.Sdk 4.0+ no longer supports VSTest by default**. The new Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the only runner. `vstest.console.exe` cannot discover or run tests from assemblies built with MSTest.Sdk 4.x because the VSTest adapter/infrastructure is no longer included.\n \nTo work around this, I need to either migrate the CI pipeline to use `dotnet test` instead, which integrates with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, or ensure the testing platform has proper dotnet test support enabled. In earlier 3.x versions, there was a workaround using `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`, but that option is no longer available in 4.0.","outputTokens":700,"requestId":"0C00:69BE5:B099C3:CD4C08:69F024E6"},"id":"a3f277d7-3e7b-4e7a-a44c-27dc6c6f4e65","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:09:43.003Z","parentId":"32ac806f-541c-40a8-a88f-09f23c9b2132"}
